{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_brookland_ver01/data/sn84026749/00222254711/1930070701/0459.xml":{"full_text":"HEARST LETS PUBLIC INVEST IN HIS GREAT CHAIN OF NEWSPAPERS\nPUBLISHER FOLLOWS NEW\nTREND-WILL FORD DO SAME?\n(Copyright, 19X0. by Unlvermil\nj Service, lee.)\nBy MERRYLE S. RUKEYSER\nNEW YORK. July 7. \u2014The\nsignificant events of finance\nare frequently undramatic.\nThe changes that alter the\nway that plain men and wo\nmen live come quietly and un\nobtrusively. For example, since\nthe war there has been a radi\ncal change in the character of\nownership in the United States.\nTitle to corporate property has\ntended to pass out of the hands\nof an oligarchy of the super\nwealthy and to \u2022be diffused\nwidely among the multitudes.\nReferring to this quiet gradual\nprocess, T. N. Carver, sagacious\neconomist of Harvard Univer\nsity, described the trend as the\n\u201cpresent economic revolution in\nthe United States.\"\nEmployes Get Stock\nThe broader significance of\nthe offering today of 2,000,-\n000 shares at $25 a share (of\nwhich 400,000 have been reserved\nfor officers and employes) of\nHearst Consolidated Publica\ntions, a new holding company\nembracing 10 of the most suc\ncess! u 1 newspapers in the\nHearst chain, the lucrative\nAmerican Weekly, and the\nAmerican Newsprint Company,\nis that it is a step toward the\nmutualization of the great\nnewspaper properties hitherto\nowned solely by William Ran\ndolph Hearst.\nRecognizing the sociological\nadvantages of partnership with\npatrons and employes, Mr.\nHearst has set up a new cor\nporate device to make the new\ncommunity of interest feasible.\nFar more important nation\nally than the sale of $50,000,000\nof securities with the coopera\ntion of a strong banking group\nis the indorsement placed by\nMr. Hearst on the newer ten\ndencies of finance.\nTouch Lives of People\nEmulating the great public\nutilities which have successfully\nengaged in customer ownership.\nMr. Hearst has applied the\nprinciple to a great coalition of\nindustrial enterprises, if news\npapers may be considered in\ndustrials.\nThough technically indus\ntrials, newspapers are of neces\nsity impregnated with a public\ninterest, and touch the lives of\nthe people far more intimately\nthan so-called public utilities\nand, in my opinion, more sig\nnificantly and intimately than\nmany of the institutions of\ngovernment itself.\nMoreover, though the public\naccept monopolistic public serv\nice institutions because there is\nno choice, the public in its\nnewspaper preferences exercises\nfreedom of the will. Newspaper\ncirculations are founded on the\nhabits and voluntary preferences\nof the public.\nIn most cities, the public can\nchoose between at least two\nnewspapers, and in the larger\ncities it has a widei choice.\nAccordingly, huge circulations\nthrough the year are proof posi\ntive of consumer acceptance,\nthe intangible which profit\nmakers in all \u2019ndustries sedu\nlously seek.\nAn \u201cEssential\" Business\nIn times of recession, there is\nan increased tendency on the\npart of investors to seek out\nsecurities of corporations en\ngaged in essential businesses.\nNewspaper making is one of\nthese. There is no disposition\nat any stage of the cycle to dis\ncontinue or postpc newspaper\nreading.\nIn an era of high prices,\nnewspapers bizarrely have per\nsistently sold f\u00ab below the\ncost of production, being sup\nported to a large measure by\nrevenues from advertisers.\nEmphasizing the distinctly,\ncustomer ownership phases of\nthe financing, Mr. Hearst has\narranged to make available the\nnew 7 per cent cumulative par\nticipating preferred stock (par\nticipating up to 10 per cent),\nat the cashier\u2019s office of any\nHearst corporation, as well as\nat any of the offices of the\nNational City Company, the\nBank of Italy, Crocker First\nNational Bank of San Francisco,\nAnglo and London-Paris Na\ntional Bank of San Francisco,\nContinental Illinois Bank and\nTrust Company of Chicago, and\nBank of America of California.\nIn addition to stressing the cus\ntomer ownership side, Mr.\nHearst has invited his business\nexecutives, editors. special\nwriters, reporters, copy readers\nand the whole miscellany of\n20,000 persons directly depen\ndent on the Hearst activities\nfor a 'ivelihood, to subscribe on\nthe easy payment plan over 24\nmonths.\nImpressive Earnings\nThe proposed issue is render\ned attractive by the splendid\nrecord of earnings over a peri\nod of years of these properties,\nwhich represent the cream of\nthe most important chain of\nnewspapers in the world.\nWith more than 42 years of\npublishing experience behind\nhim. Mr. Hearst is unquestion\nably the foremost world figure\nin popular journalism.\nTo those who want my hard\nboiled investment opinion of\nissue, I can say that when\nI was tentatively asked wheth\ner as an employe I would be\ninterested in subscribing. I re\nplied that I would take the\nmaximum amount offered to\nme. The employe ownership\nphase is especially attractive\nfor it weds to the organization\nvalued men and women, who\notherwise might feel freer to\ndrift with the tides.\nA widespread feeling on the\npart of ambitious persons that\nthey are working for them\nselves and sharing in the prof\nits adds to the dignity of pro\nfessional labor, and is of im\nmense value to the organiza\ntion not only in elevating mo\nrale, but also in reducing the\nwastes of excessive labor turn\nover.\nWill Ford Follow?\nMr. Hearst\u2019s move today con\nstitutes a landmark tn the his\ntory of public aspects of finance,\nbecause until now he was one\nof the few who adhered to the\nolder system of sole proprietor\nship, whereas other companies\nengaged in public financing.\nHenry Ford Is another conspicu\nous example of those who have\nstayed apart.\nThough a Wall Street bank\ning house some years ago of\nfered to sell a billion dollars of\nsecurities of the Ford Motor\nCompany, stock ownership is\nstill held exclusively by Henry\nand his son, Edsel. Will the\nFord Company be the next to\nstep in line?\nThe size of the new holding\ncorporation emphasizes the ex\ntent' to which publishing has\nbecome a big business, with\ncolossal earnings for the success\nful and immense property in\nvestments. Pub 1i s hing has\npassed far from the pioneer\ndays when it reflected only the\nwhims and idiosyncrasies of a\nnot wholly responsible editor.\nMany properities have become\nmere bu s i ness institutions\u2014\noverorganized and over-routi\nnized.\nMr. Hearst\u2019s rare genius has\nbeen in combining business\nacumen with editorial zeal and\na flaming passion for espousing\npublic causes.\nMr. Hearst, who has demon\nstrated these many years his\namazing record as a profit\nmaker, will retain the voting\nstock and continue to act as\npilot. The \u201cA\u201d preferred stock\nis nonvoting, unless the dividend\nshould be omitted four consecu\ntive times. The company has\nbeen earning the dividend on\nthe $50,000,000 of preferred more\nthan three times over in the last\nfour years.\nThe new company is a Dela\nware corporation, with an autho\nrized capitalization of $100,000.-\n000. divided into $100,000,000\n\u201cA\u201d or preferred stock, of which\nhalf will be presently Issued,\nand 2,000,000 shares of com\nmon stock, no par value all\nof the lattter of which will go\nto the Star holding corporation,\nwhich is ultimately owned by\nMr. Hearst.\nThe other $50,000,000 of pre\nferred stock will be reserved and\nwill be issued only for the pur\npose of retiring outstanding\nbonded indebtedness at the call\nprice.\nThe preferred stock is cumu\nlative up to 7 per cent, and non\ncumulative on the additional 3\nper cent. The book value of the\nproperties going into the new\ncorporation is $100,000,000.\nsecukSs\"\nIndnztrial aad Miac*U*a*M9\nNet\nHigh Ix>w Lazt Chg*\nAller Cp war wd 5% 5% 5%\nAm Laun 2% 2% 2%\nAm Austin Car.. 6% S I\nAm Corp 1% 1%\nAm Earle H\nAndes 35 .30 .35 .05\nAppal Gas war., 3% 3% 3%\nAsad 