 6%s 75%\nRome 6%s 90%\nSao Paulo City o%s 89\nSeine Department 7s 107%\nSerbia 7s 84%\nSoissons Is 104%\nSweden 5%s 105%\nSwiss Confederation 8s 107%\nToho Electric 7s JOO\nlAuguay 6s 95\nUruguay 8s 106%\nYokohama 6s 96%\nOIL STOCKS\n(Furnished by W. B. Hibbs A Co.)\nBid? j Ask?\nBorne Scrymser I 20 21\nBuckeye Pipe Line I 55 57\nCheeeboro Mfg Co |l4O |l5O\nContinental OH 11% I 15%\nCumberland Pipe Line 30 40\nEureka Pipe Lin 40 42\nGalena Signal OH com 3%| 5%\nHumble Oil 85 81\nHis. Pipe Line- |3OO |315\nImperial Oil Canada I 20 20%\nIndiana Pipe Line I 32 34\nInternational Pete I 18%| 18%\nNational Traneit 16 17%\nN. Y. Transportation...'.... 12% 17\nNorthern Pipe Lines 35 41\nOhio OH 64% 65%\nPenna Mex Fuel 19 19%\nSolar Ref Co 13 15%\nSouthern Pipe Line 15 17\nSouth Penn Oil 36 38\nSoutheastern Pipe Line 41 52\nStandard OH of Indiana.... 50 50%\nStandard Oil of Kentucky.. 31% 32\nStandard Oil of Nebraska... 45% 47\nStandard Oil of Ohio 78 82\nStandard Oil of Ohio pfd... 117% 119\nSwan A Fink 5 10\nVacuum OH 81% 82%\nCHICAGO LIVESTOCK\nCHICAGO, July 7 (I.N.S.).\u2014Hogs:\nReceipts. 31.000; market, 10c higher.\nTop, 39.30; bulk, 39.3509.71; heavy\nweight, 81.2509.75; medium weight,\n89.1009.30; light weight, 89,8509.80;\nlight lights, 89.3109.75; packing eowe,\nef.IIOI.lS; pigs, 83.1009.11; holdovers.\n2,000.\nCattle\u2014Receipts 8,400: market, 25%\n50c lower. Calves: Receipts, 2,000;\nmarket, steady. Beef steers: Good and\nchoice, 811.013.50; common and med\nium. 37010.50; yearlings, 87013.\nButcher cattle: Heifers, 31.10010.50;\ncowe, 84.7107; bulls. 36.B0OI.50;\ncalves. 39011: feeder steers, 81-50010;\nstacker steers, 8009.50; Stocker cows\nand helfere. 84.3001.\nSheep\u2014 Receipts. 10,000; market,\nsteady. Medium and choice lambs,\n810011: culls and common. 85#8;\nyearlings. 8<O9; common and choice\newes. 3203.19; feeder lambs, 37.590\n1.50.\nTAo Ntttiital Dmly\nHlrh Low Dividend Rat* Hlrh Low 1:1S Cb\u2019Se\n744 32 Coeden Oil H 4 344 344-14\n74 54 Cr\u0