of a business\nrevival is the extreme pessimism\nthat pervades the business world\nat the present time, according to\nthe Alexander Hamilton Institute.\nIn the past, business sentiment\nhas always been excessively pes\nsimistic prior to an upturn in\nbusiness just as overoptimism has\nalways preceded a slump. It\nwill be recalled that business men\nwere as optimistic last summer\nas this summer they are pessi\nmistic.\nBusiness indicators which have\ncome to hand during the past\nweek have not been unanimously\nfavorable. Creeks cashed outside\nNew York city for the week\nended June 25 amounted to $5,\u00ab\n810,000,000 as compared with $5,-\n708,000,000 a year ago, an in\ncrease of 1.8 per cent. Since the\nbeginning of June checks cashed\nhave shown a steady improve\nment as compared with a year\nago. The changes from last year\nfor each of the past four weeks\nwere as follows: ---18.4 per cent,\n\u201410.2 per cent, \u20145.4 per cent,\n1.8 per cent\nAnother encouraging feature\nhas been the Increase in com\nmercial loans for two successive\nweeks. Commercial loans by re\nporting member banks on June\n25 amounted to $8,572,000,000 as\ncompared with $9,139,000,000 a\nyear ago, a decrease of 6.2 per\ncent. This compares with a de\ncrease from last year of 8.2 per\ncent on June 11.\nKnit \u2018Wool\u2019 Labels\nMust Tell Content\n\u201cWool\u201d labels on knit under\nwear hereafter must tell how\nmuch wool the garments contain.\nA rule of business practice\nadopted by the knit underwear in\ndustry and approved by the Fed\neral Trade Commission, which\nmade it public yesterday, prohib\nits use of the term unless the\n\u201cpercentage by weight of wool\u201d is\nstated. It will be made effective\ni January 1.\n19","height":"30453","width":"24279"}}
